		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>26 Aug 1850</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I had sent my letter to the letters<lb/> Office this morning when <persName>Mr Simmonds</persName> sent me<lb/> a pack containing the Occident &#38;c &#38;c &#38; your kind<lb/> favor of <date>July 3d</date> the vessel that brought the parcel<lb/> arrived on the <date>22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi></date> the pack for me must have been<lb/> contained in his &#38; he was kind enough to keep<lb/> mine 4 days&#44; pitifully enough&#8212;therefore in future<lb/> please send mine direct.</p>
			<p>I have read with much interest the review<lb/> &#38; was glad that one honorable &#38; high minded man<lb/> was found to defend you &#38; uphold the ministry&#44;<lb/> his name should be published&#44; for honor is due<lb/> to him for the spirited manner he shows up the<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> adjunto&#59; now that the affair &#38;<lb/> Resolution is printed I feel persuaded that the<lb/> actors most regret the step taken. I am held out<lb/> in this opinion by the election being postponed<lb/> for such a length of time&#44; it appears that they<lb/> anticipate an arrangement with you. I council you<lb/> by all means to be firm on the point&#44; for I am<lb/> persuaded that the more it is discussed the greater<lb/> will be the increase of opinion in your favor&#44; I have<lb/> fought nearly the same battle here &#38; after much<lb/> difficulty succeeded in placing the minister <del>in his</del></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>as to his ecclesiastical duties above Parnas &#38;<lb/> adjunta as you will perceive by our code of<lb/> laws&#8212;it should be so&#44; if we desire to have<lb/> Respectable men at our head</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I regret that any man having his dignity<lb/> as a Minister in view could be found to offer<lb/> himself under the propositions set forth. <persName>Mr DeSola</persName><lb/> it appears has not yet known off the trammels of<lb/> the <add>&#63;</add> Congregation I pity him&#44; &#38; could never<lb/> bring myself to respect his ministers&#44; the other Gentlemen<lb/> I know little of</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">All these circumstances lend to detract from<lb/> the dignity of our people. I wish as the Prophet says<lb/> we would become wise.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I will send to <placeName>New York</placeName> for the Asmoneon<lb/> with best wishes Remain yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">A Wolff</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
          
